General interval comment: Foraminifera particularly concentrated in a fine layer at 23 cm.
Predominately dark grey with rare inclusions of redder clay (41-47 cm) and lateral variation from lighter to darker grey.

Top 5 cm grade from the dark gray muddy foraminiferal ooze with nannofossils of the previous section to the lighter grey clayey foraminiferal ooze with nannofossils of the current section. Heavy bioturbation with rare inclusions of darker grey clay-rich sediments, lighter grey foraminifer rich inclusions. Color varies throughout, through various shades of grey.
Lighter relatively foram rich interval in Section 2, color between N 6 and N 7.

Interval varies between redder to greener (10YR 5/1) lithologies, with particularly reddish inclusions at 61-121 cm.
Interval has a mottled and somewhat layered appearence sue to the inclusion or redder (5Y 6/1) to greener (10Y 5/1 to 10Y 5/2) intervals.

Interval varies between redder (10YR 5/2) to greener (10Y 6/1) sediment. Rare black blebs (pyrite) throughout section.

Rare small pebbles.  Redder mottles are 10YR 4/2.

Smear slides identify this interval as a clayey foraminiferal ooze with nannofossils but with an elevated silt abundance in comparsion to surrounding sections.

Similar to preceding interval but with a smoother appearance due to clay content.  Faint green horizons at 63-69 cm and prominent green horizon at 126 cm. Black sulfide blebs scattered throughout this interval.
